Add boiling water to gelatin mix in large bowl; stir 2 minutes until completely dissolved. Add enough ice to cold water to measure 1-1/2 cups. Add to gelatin; stir until ice is completely melted. Place oranges in 6-cup mold sprayed with cooking spray; cover with 2 cups gelatin. Refrigerate 45 minutes or until gelatin is set but not firm. Meanwhile, refrigerate remaining gelatin 45 minutes or until slightly thickened. Whisk in 2 cups COOL WHIP until well blended. Pour over gelatin layer in mold. Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm. Unmold. Serve topped with remaining COOL WHIP.